podcast called "Q'ed Up."

00:36:55.520 --> 00:36:59.480
Q apostrophe E-D Up,
because it's from KQED.

00:36:59.480 --> 00:37:00.146
PJ VOGT: Oh, OK.

00:37:00.146 --> 00:37:02.430
Yeah, that could be better.

00:37:02.430 --> 00:37:14.130
ALEX GOLDMAN: But
it is about the way

00:37:14.130 --> 00:37:17.100
that San Francisco has priced
out so many people that they've

00:37:17.100 --> 00:37:21.030
moved to suburbs, and how the
previously white suburbs have

00:37:21.030 --> 00:37:21.582
dealt with--

00:37:21.582 --> 00:37:23.040
PJ VOGT: It's such
a weird dystopia

00:37:23.040 --> 00:37:24.700
that we're making
every city unlivable

00:37:24.700 --> 00:37:27.901
but then making really
good podcasts about it.

00:37:27.901 --> 00:37:30.150
ALEX GOLDMAN: Well, you know,
whatever works, I guess.

00:37:30.150 --> 00:37:31.733
PJ VOGT: I don't
know that that works.

00:37:31.733 --> 00:37:34.170
ALEX GOLDMAN: Yeah,
the world is terrible,

00:37:34.170 --> 00:37:35.870
but it's nice that
it's documented.

00:37:35.870 --> 00:37:37.370
PJ VOGT: But the
podcasts are great.

00:37:37.370 --> 00:37:38.760
ALEX GOLDMAN: Yeah.

00:37:38.760 --> 00:37:42.009
So those are both really good.

00:37:42.009 --> 00:37:42.550
I don't know.

00:37:42.550 --> 00:37:44.100
"The Bone Zone" is good, guys.

00:37:44.100 --> 00:37:46.090
SPEAKER 1: What is
"The Bone Zone" about?

00:37:46.090 --> 00:37:47.540
PJ VOGT: What is "The
Bone Zone" about, Alex?

00:37:47.540 --> 00:37:49.290
SPEAKER 1: I mean, how
good is that title?

00:37:49.290 --> 00:37:50.880
Is it accurate?

00:37:50.880 --> 00:37:54.369
ALEX GOLDMAN: It's
two guys who just--

00:37:54.369 --> 00:37:55.660
PJ VOGT: It's "The Jerky Boys."

00:37:55.660 --> 00:37:58.035
ALEX GOLDMAN: It's a little
better than "The Jerky Boys."

00:37:58.035 --> 00:38:00.180
It's two guys who make
prank phone calls.

00:38:00.180 --> 00:38:02.160
PJ VOGT: They call Hugo Boss
and try to boss people around.

00:38:02.160 --> 00:38:03.840
ALEX GOLDMAN: They call Hugo
Boss and try and boss people

00:38:03.840 --> 00:38:04.470
around.

00:38:04.470 --> 00:38:08.850
They call Red Lobster
and say, do you guys

00:38:08.850 --> 00:38:10.410
have the lobster
on lobster anymore?

